Here is a simple Visual C++ program using WinAPI to create a graphical window that displays a custom message and an exit button when a file with a certain extension is opened.

Step 1: Create a new Visual C++ Win32 Project in Visual Studio
Open Visual Studio, click "Create new project," select "C++," and then "Win32 Project." Give the project a name and click "OK."

